{"questionId":"3958","questionHtml":"<p>A system that consists of a single spring stores a total elastic potential energy <em>E</em><sub>p</sub> when a load&nbsp;is added to the spring. Another identical spring connected in parallel is added to the system. The same load is now applied to the parallel springs.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/840fcaa90aed8d25b2392bc6381408ee8609a9a6.png\"></p>\n<p>What is the total elastic potential energy stored in the changed system?</p>\n<p>A. <em>E</em><sub>p</sub></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{E_p}}}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>E</mi>\n          <mi>p</mi>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{E_p}}}{4}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>E</mi>\n          <mi>p</mi>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{E_p}}}{8}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>E</mi>\n          <mi>p</mi>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>8</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3958","referenceCode":"17N.1.SL.TZ0.7","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A system that consists of a single spring stores a total elastic potential energy Ep when a load is added to the spring. Another identical spring connected in parallel is added to ","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"7","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics","2.3 – Work, energy, and power","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},